Description: 
        
        Introduction
        ============
        
        An installable theme for Plone 3.0 by CANAIMA GNU/Linux Website
        
        Based on the Canaima Aponwao theme Luis Alejandro Martínez Faneyth
        (http://huntingbears.co.cc/).
        
        This theme has not gone through the rounds of browser testing
        so it should be considered an alpha release.
        
        Luis Alejandro Martínez Faneyth was based on a WordPress theme
        called FREEmium released for free by FreebiesDock.com
        Authors: Paul Kadysz (design) and Dariusz Siedlecki (frontend)
        
        
        
        
        canaima.aponwaotheme Installation
        ---------------------------------
        
        To install canaima.aponwaotheme into the global Python environment (or a workingenv),
        using a traditional Zope 2 instance, you can do this:
        
        * When you're reading this you have probably already run
        ``easy_install canaima.aponwaotheme``. Find out how to install setuptools
        (and EasyInstall) here:
        http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/EasyInstall
        
        * If you are using Zope 2.9 (not 2.10), get `pythonproducts`_ and install it
        via::
        
        python setup.py install --home /path/to/instance
        
        into your Zope instance.
        
        * Create a file called ``canaima.aponwaotheme-configure.zcml`` in the
        ``/path/to/instance/etc/package-includes`` directory.  The file
        should only contain this::
        
        <include package="canaima.aponwaotheme" />
        
        .. _pythonproducts: http://plone.org/products/pythonproducts
        
        
        Alternatively, if you are using zc.buildout and the plone.recipe.zope2instance
        recipe to manage your project, you can do this:
        
        * Add ``canaima.aponwaotheme`` to the list of eggs to install, e.g.:
        
        [buildout]
        ...
        eggs =
        ...
        canaima.aponwaotheme
        
        * Tell the plone.recipe.zope2instance recipe to install a ZCML slug:
        
        [instance]
        recipe = plone.recipe.zope2instance
        ...
        zcml =
        canaima.aponwaotheme
        
        * Re-run buildout, e.g. with:
        
        $ ./bin/buildout
        
        You can skip the ZCML slug if you are going to explicitly include the package
        from another package's configure.zcml file.
        
        
